The Federal Government has expressed readiness to cooperate with the African Union to advance science and technology innovations to combat poverty and underdevelopment on the continent. The Minister of Science and Technology, Dr Ogbonnaya Onu disclosed  this when the Commissioner of the Human Resources, Science and Technology Department (HRST) of the African Union Commission   (AUC) Prof. Sarah Anyang paid him a courtesy visit  in Abuja yesterday. Dr Onu commended the AU for spearheading Africa to move in a new direction, adding that with abundant materials resources, African nations must embrace a knowledge and innovation driven economy in order to add value and diversify her economy. Prof, Sarah Anyang had stressed the need for Nigeria and AU to work together “In the march of progress for Africa we want, Africa that we envisage and the paradise that African can become”.   